                            <comment id="12712986" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 26 May 2009 13:33:21 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Background?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12712988" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 26 May 2009 13:42:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;yonik mentioned it would be a good idea back when I added reopen in, kind of as a failsafe. I pushed it into 243, but it doesnt really belong there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reopen has now been in use some, and I think a failsafe is less of a concern, but it could still come in handy - when we allow custom IndexReaders,&lt;br/&gt;
there may be a reason to not reopen it. Or if we find a new Lucene reopen bug or something when someone is doing something obscure, &lt;br/&gt;
1.4 users will be able to turn it off rather than jumping to trunk for a fix or waiting for 1.4.1 or whatever.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
